    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Subphylum of small marine animals found throughout the seas of the world. Most are underwater saclike filter feeders, although some are predators. Like other chordates, they have develop a notochord early in their development.  Adult members are commonly embedded in a tough secreted tunic containing cellulose. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>屬於小型海生動物的亞門，可見於世界各地的海域。大多數為水中的囊狀濾食動物，但部份為食肉動物。與其他的脊索動物相同，在早期的演化過程中，演化出一條脊索。成體通常以一層分泌而成、厚實含有纖維質的被囊所包覆。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
